def smallerNumbersThanCurrent(nums):
    result = [0] * len(nums)
    for i in range(len(nums)):
        for j in range(len(nums)):
            if nums[j] < nums[i]:
                result[i] += 1
    return result
```

    The algorithm iterates through each number in the input array (nums) using a nested loop. For each number (nums[i]), it checks if another number (nums[j]) in the array is smaller than it (nums[j] < nums[i]) and increments the count if it is. The count of smaller numbers for each nums[i] is stored in the result array, which is returned at the end.

